h3. Summary
Since sub-tasks are directly related to their parents, those should be displayed in hierarchic order on the *Issue Navigator*. Something similar is already applied on Agile boards, for example.

h3. Workaround
It's possible to use the [Script Runner plug-in|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.onresolve.jira.groovy.groovyrunner] to achieve this by adding a _Scripted Field_ to the sub-tasks, storing the Parent Issue's key.

{panel}
Here's the script:
{code:java}
import com.atlassian.jira.issue.Issue;

Issue parentIssue = issue.getParentObject();
def parentIssueKey, issueKey;

if (parentIssue != null) {
	parentIssueKey = parentIssue.getKey();
    return parentIssueKey;
}
else {
    issueKey = issue.getKey();
    return issueKey;
}
{code}

And here's the JQL operand you should append to filters for this ordering to be applied:
{code:sql}
ORDER BY "Parent Issue Key" ASC, key ASC
{code}
{panel}

(!) _Please note that Atlassian *does not* provide any kind of support to third-party add-ons or scripting of any kind, so we *cannot guarantee* any further assistance or maintenance on this script._

