I'm trying to use a confluence template to generate a jiraissues URL.  I'd like to specify the search for "fixfor" by string, instead of numeric id.  For example, taking the example search for "jira issues fixed in the latest version", and looking at the "XML" url path...

http://jira.atlassian.com/secure/IssueNavigator.jspa?view=rss&&pid=10240&fixfor=11351  [ ... rest deleted ]

I'd rather not require the person using the template to know that "3.4 Pro" is 10240.   I'd rather just have them fill in the version as a string in a replacement var, and then be able to insert that into the jiraissues url path.  (If URI encoding is an issue, let it be an issue.  We'll use version strings that don't have spaces or other "weird" characters)

